  "prompt": "What is the best way to substitute celery seeds in a recipe?",
  "response": "Here are some good substitutes for celery seeds:\n\n1. Fresh celery (chopped)\n- Best flavor match\n- Use about 3 times more volume than seeds\n- Works well in soups, stews, and salads\n\n2. Celery salt\n- Similar flavor profile\n- Reduce added salt in recipe\n- Good for dry rubs and seasoning blends\n\n3. Dill seeds\n- Similar texture and mild flavor\n- Good in pickling and seed-based recipes\n\n4. Caraway seeds\n- Similar earthy flavor\n- Works well in savory dishes\n\n5. Dried lovage leaves\n- Strong celery-like flavor\n- Use sparingly\n\n6. Fennel seeds\n- Slightly different flavor but similar texture\n- Good in spice blends\n\nThe best substitute depends on the specific recipe and desired flavor profile. Consider the dish's overall taste and adjust accordingly.",
